\f1\b\fs40 \cf2 Chapter 1
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 The Mapleaf Knows
\f0\b0 \
\

\fs28 It was an ordinary Tuesday in Whisperwood.\
\
By the river, Sage was watching tadpoles. She did this most mornings. She never got bored of it.\
\
In the branches above her, Pip was trying to leap from one tree to the next without using his hands. He had already fallen twice. He was going to try a third time.\
\
Nearby, Vera sat with her back against the Mapleaf tree, making a list of everything she knew. It was a very long list.\
\
She glanced up at the Mapleaf\'92s veins the way she always did \'97 just to check. They were golden and calm.\
\
Good.\
\
She looked back at her list.\
\
Then she looked up again.\
\
The veins had gone dark.\
\
The village of Whisperwood had a rule.\
\
When the Mapleaf tree\'92s veins turned dark, something was coming.\
\
Vera knew this. Vera knew most things.\
\
She was back on her feet before she finished the thought, when Pip landed on her head.\
\
\'93Something is coming,\'94 said Pip.\
\
\'93I know,\'94 said Vera.\
\
\'93The Mapleaf\'97\'94\
\
\'93I know,\'94 said Vera.\
\
\'93But did you see how dark the veins are? They\'92re almost\'97\'94\
\
\'93Pip.\'94\
\
\'93Yes?\'94\
\
\'93I know.\'94\
\
Pip flicked his tail. He did not look convinced.\
