\cf2 Sage was no longer watching tadpoles.\
\
She was watching the water.\
\
It was moving faster than it should.\
\
She placed one foot in the current. Then she took it back out.\
\

\f2\i Too fast
\f0\i0 , she thought.
\f2\i Something\'92s wrong.
\f0\i0 \
\
She reached for a bellflower growing near the bank.\
\
She rang it once. Twice. Three times.\
\
In Whisperwood, three rings meant: 
\f2\i come quickly, but don\'92t panic.
\f0\i0 \
