\f1\b\fs40 \cf2 Chapter 2
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 I Already Know the Plan
\f0\b0 \
\

\fs28 Vera arrived first.\
\
This was not surprising. Vera always arrived first. She had usually already decided what to do before she got there.\
\
\'93Flooding,\'94 she said, before Sage could speak. \'93The Mapleaf showed dark veins this morning. The river is rising. We need the beavers.\'94\
\
Sage opened her mouth.\
\
\'93I\'92ll go find them,\'94 said Vera.\
\
Sage closed her mouth.\
\
Pip arrived second. He was out of breath and had a leaf stuck to his ear.\
\
\'93What did I miss?\'94 he said.\
\
\'93Vera already knows the plan,\'94 said Sage.\
\
Pip looked at the river. Then at Sage. Then at the direction Vera had already run.\
\
\'93Does she know 
\f2\i why
\f0\i0  the river is fast?\'94\
\
Sage looked at the water.\
\
\'93\'85I don\'92t think she asked,\'94 said Sage.\
