\f1\b\fs40 \cf2 Chapter 3
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 What the Rock Remembered
\f0\b0 \
\

\fs28 The beavers were busy.\
\
They were always busy.\
\
\'93Flooding?\'94 said the head beaver. His name was Bram. He had a hard hat made of bark and an expression that suggested he had seen many floods. \'93Where?\'94\
\
\'93The burrows,\'94 said Vera. \'93River\'92s rising. We need to redirect it.\'94\
\
Bram stroked his chin.\
\
\'93Can\'92t,\'94 he said. \'93Not safely. Not quickly.\'94\
\
Vera blinked.\
\
This was not part of her plan.\
\
\'93What do you mean you can\'92t\'97\'94\
\
\'93I mean,\'94 said Bram slowly, \'93that if we touch that river wrong, we make it worse. Something\'92s come down at the river bend \'97 blocking the channel. Until we can get eyes on it in the daylight, we don\'92t touch a thing.\'94\
\
Vera opened her mouth. Then closed it.\
\
This had never happened before.\
\
\
Back at the river, Pip was doing what Pip always did when there was a problem.\
\
He was trying to help.\
\
He had found a large stick. He was not entirely sure what to do with the large stick. But it felt better than standing still.\
\
\'93Pip,\'94 said Sage. \'93What are you doing?\'94\
\
\'93Helping,\'94 said Pip.\
\
\'93With a stick.\'94\
\
\'93It\'92s a big stick.\'94\
\
Sage watched the water rise another inch.\
\
\'93Come with me,\'94 she said.\
\
She led him to the oldest boulder at the river\'92s edge. It was round and grey and covered in soft moss. It had been sitting in the same spot since before anyone in Whisperwood could remember.\
\
Sage pressed her hand against it.\
\
\'93Excuse me,\'94 she said quietly.\
\
The boulder was silent for a long moment.\
\
Then, very slowly, it said:\
\
\'93\'85Tree.\'94\
\
Pip leaned in. \'93Tree? What tree?\'94\
\
They waited.\
\
The river crept higher.\
\
A mouse family hurried past with bundles on their backs.\
\
Finally the boulder spoke again.\
\
\'93\'85Fell.\'94\
